title: Shinta Ratri, Fighter for Transgender Rights in Indonesia, Dies at 60
description: The Islamic boarding school she helped found offers a haven for transgender women in a country where discrimination can be acute.

title: China to Welcome Belarusian Leader, Raising Concerns Over Ukraine
description: A state visit next week by Aleksandr G. Lukashenko of Belarus seems to confirm U.S. fears that China is prepared to send lethal aid to Russia.

title: Tempered in a Crucible of Violence, Zelensky Rises to the Moment
description: In much of the world, President Volodymyr Zelensky, once brushed off as a political lightweight, has become a household name, representing Ukraine’s tenacity and underdog victories against Russia.

title: A NATO Minnow Reels From Cyberattacks Linked to Iran
description: Albania has been the target of repeated digital assaults believed to be linked to its sheltering of an Iranian dissident group on its soil.

title: As War Passes Year Mark, Fighting Shows No Sign of Letting Up
description: Ukraine reported Russian attacks along the front line and warned that the risk of missile strikes was still high across the country. Protests over the war were planned through the weekend.

title: War in Ukraine Deepens Divide Among Major Economies at G20 Gathering
description: Treasury Secretary Janet L. Yellen urged her counterparts at a summit in India to condemn Russia’s actions, and she defended the cost of supplying aid to Kyiv.

title: Getting Back on Skis
description: Returning to activities you’ve given up can be a surprising source of confidence and wonder.

title: For the First Time in 52 Years, There’s No Skating Through the Capital
description: A winter of gyrating temperatures and rainfalls caused officials to give up on the “world’s largest skating rink.”

title: Their Hair Long and Flowing or in Ponytails, Women in Iran Flaunt Their Locks
description: Defiant resistance to Iran’s mandatory hijab law has exploded across the country after nationwide protests that erupted last year.

title: In Nigeria’s Presidential Election, A Rare Chance to Turn the Corner
description: In Nigeria’s presidential election on Saturday, voters are desperate to elect a leader who can unleash their youthful country’s potential and chart a new course after years of dashed hopes.

title: The Salton Sea, an Accident of History, Faces a New Water Crisis
description: The vast California lake relies on runoff from cropland to avoid disappearing. But as farmers face water cuts due to drought and an ever drier Colorado River, the Salton Sea stands to lose again.

title: Protests and Defiance Mark a Year of Russia’s War on Ukraine
description: On the anniversary of the invasion, Volodymyr Zelensky held a marathon news conference and vowed victory if Ukraine’s allies remained united “like a fist.”

title: Biden Reaffirms Support for Ukraine Amid Concerns About Russia-Iran Ties
description: The Biden administration announced new measures targeting Moscow and supporters of President Vladimir V. Putin’s war.

title: Doctor Denounces C.I.A. Practice of ‘Rectal Feeding’ of Prisoners
description: In a hearing at Guantánamo Bay, an expert gave a graphic public depiction of torture after the Sept. 11, 2001, terror attacks.

title: Robert Hébras, Last Survivor of 1944 Massacre in France, Dies at 97
description: Dead bodies shielded him as the Nazis killed 643 people in Oradour-sur-Glane. He spent his life keeping the memory of the slaughter alive.
